To cite this model code and repository in publications use:

  Gelber, S., Tietjen, B., & May, F. (2025). Disturbance and landscape 
  characteristics interactively drive dispersal strategies in continuous 
  and fragmented metacommunities. [Journal Name]. [DOI]

A BibTeX entry for LaTeX users is:

  @Article{gelber2025dispersal,
    title = {Disturbance and landscape characteristics interactively drive dispersal strategies in continuous and fragmented metacommunities},
    author = {Stav Gelber and Britta Tietjen and Felix May},
    journal = {[Journal Name]},
    year = {2025},
    volume = {},
    number = {},
    pages = {},
    doi = {},
    url = {https://github.com/Stavooo/Gelber_etal_2025_dispersal},
  }

Please also cite the related publication on geometric and demographic fragmentation effects:

  Gelber, S., Blowes, S. A., Chase, J. M., Huth, A., Schurr, F. M., 
  Tietjen, B., Zeller, J. W., & May, F. (2023). Geometric and demographic 
  effects explain contrasting fragmentation-biodiversity relationships 
  across scales. [Journal details if published]
